The paper focuses on analyzing user behavior in Q&A instances, which falls under the scope of social computing (cs.SOC) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The authors also mention the importance of optimizing Q&A community building efforts, which could be related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and cybersecurity (cs.CYBER) in terms of ensuring the quality and safety of information exchanged in these communities. Finally, the paper's emphasis on characterizing user behavior through time series analysis aligns with the subfield of social informatics (cs.SI).
